    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><p><i>17th-level Way of Mercy feature</i></p><p>Your mastery of life energy opens the door to the ultimate mercy. As an action, you can touch the corpse of a creature that died within the past 24 hours and expend 5 ki points. The creature then returns to life, regaining a number of hit points equal to [[/r 4d10]] + your Wisdom modifier. If the creature died while subject to any of the following conditions, it revives with them removed: &amp;Reference[condition=blinded], &amp;Reference[condition=deafened], &amp;Reference[condition=paralyzed], &amp;Reference[condition=poisoned], and &amp;Reference[condition=stunned].</p><p>Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a long rest.</p></div>",
